<p><b>How many developmental stages were described by Santrock 2002?</b> Santrock also discusses 8 developmental periods: prenatal, infancy, early childhood, middle/late childhood, adolescence, early adulthood, middle adulthood, and late adulthood. The document provides details on the physical, cognitive, and psychosocial characteristics and developmental tasks of each life stage.</p>